get_wire_variation_mode(25.10)                  get_wire_variation_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_wire_variation_mode

Syntax
       get_wire_variation_mode

       [-help]

        [-corner_sigma_multiplier]

        [-correlation_type]

        [-disable_positive_slack_shift]

       [-enable_seperate_wire_var_sigma_multiplier]

        [-layer_avg_rpt]

        [-rc_correlation_factor]

        [-reset]

       [-use_nsigma_coupling_capacitance]

        [-use_nsigma_slew_for_timing_check]

       [-wire_cell_variation_correlation]

        [-wire_var_reporting_sigma_multiplier]

        [-quiet]

        [-nonDefault]

       Displays  the following information about the specified set_wire_varia-
       tion_mode command parameters in the Tempus log file and the Tempus con-
       sole:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify any parameters, the software displays information
       for all of the parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       parameter_names
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See set_wire_variation_mode for descriptions of  the  parameters
              you can specify.

Related Information
              * set_wire_variation_mode

